            "Step 2: Data encoding and scaling is successful!\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "In this step, I performed One-Hot Encoding to convert categorical text data into numerical format. Most importantly, I applied Standard Scaling. Since SVM is a distance-based algorithm, it requires all features to be on the same scale (like Age and Cholesterol) to work correctly. Without scaling, the SVM model's accuracy would drop significantly."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "u5ABBEnDePk9"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Initialize SVM with RBF kernel\n",
        "# RBF is used for handling non-linear relationships in medical data\n",
        "svm_model = SVC(kernel='rbf', C=1.0, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Train the model\n",
        "svm_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Predict on test data\n",
        "y_pred = svm_model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Final Accuracy Score\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report\n",
        "print(f\"SVM Model Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.2f}\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nClassification Report:\\n\", classification_report(y_test, y_pred))"
